cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.NI, cs.PL 

The paper deals with scheduling multiple applications to share the same GPU, which is a problem in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses memory constraints, which suggests that it could belong to cs.OS (Operating Systems). The use of GPUs in the paper could also place it in cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes policies for scheduling, which could place it in cs.PL (Programming Languages).
